rca of the issue:
AssetDetail.jsx uses `const isNew = id === 'new';` and `const [editing, setEditing] = useState(isNew);`. On a new-asset save, api.post succeeds, then navigate(`/assets/${data.id}`) swaps the URL param. Component does NOT unmount — it's the same <Route path='/assets/:id'> — so useState 'editing' retains its previous value (true). useEffect([id]) fires loadAsset() which correctly sets form/original but never touches `editing`. Fix: add `setEditing(false)` immediately after navigate in the isNew branch of save(), e.g.:

  if (isNew) {
    const { data } = await api.post('/assets', payload);
    toast.success(`Asset ${data.asset_id} created`);
    navigate(`/assets/${data.id}`);
    setEditing(false);
  }

This lets the locked-mode UI (Edit button, LOCKED badge, ReadField views) render as designed.
